    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="798"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Hungary)/7–1345:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 798<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Representative in Hungary</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SHFA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-17T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Your 281<note n="1" xml:id="d798fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d311">Document No. 311, printed in vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and 286<note n="2" xml:id="d798fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d794fn6">document No. 794, footnote 6</ref>.</note> July 13
                    have been repeated to Potsdam together with <gloss target="#t_Depts1"
                        >Depts</gloss> views to the effect that the Russian “order of procedure”
                    appears to cover several of the points we had suggested, notably provision for
                    tripartite agreement on policy directives, but that the language was not
                    entirely satisfactory. While unilateral revision of statutes is of course not in
                    conformity with our position as one of the parties to their original
                    negotiation, we believe Soviet proposals form good basis for tripartite
                    discussion and agreement on revised statutes for second period.</p>
                <p>Any further clarification which <persName corresp="#p_KMGWS1">Key</persName> may
                    obtain should be telegraphed Potsdam through military as well as <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>. It is assumed that he will take no action
                    implying acceptance of the Russian revision pending appropriate instructions.
                    (Re your 291 July 16<note n="3" xml:id="d798fn3">
                        <ref target="#d795">Document No. 795</ref>.</note>). Meanwhile <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> hopes that political aspect can be worked out
                    at Potsdam along lines of our and Genl <persName corresp="#p_KMGWS1"
                        >Key</persName>’s proposals (<gloss target="#t_Deptels1">Deptels</gloss> 57
                    May 28<note n="4" xml:id="d798fn4">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d287fn5"
                            >vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, document No. 287, footnote
                        5</ref>.</note> and 124 June 23<note n="5" xml:id="d798fn5">See <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#d294fn3">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            document No. 294, footnote 3</ref>.</note>) with details to be worked
                    out later in Moscow or Budapest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RS1">S[amuel] R[eber]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
